Objective:

  • To identify different segments in the existing customer based on their spending patterns as well as past interaction with the bank.
  • To run customer targetted advertisement and aswell upselling the existing customer.
  • Upgrade the service delivery Model.

Back Ground: Data collected has customers credit limit, number of credit cards, customer contact through visiting bank, online banking and through call center.

Dataset: ALLLife bank

Data Description: Data is of various customers of a bank with their credit limit, the total number of credit cards the customer has, and different channels through which customer has contacted the bank for any queries, different channels include visiting the bank, online and through a call centre.

Task:

  1. Perform EDA
  2. Apply Clustering Mechanism.
  3. Compare different clustering mechanism
  4. Provide Insights to the bank.

Order of Notebook

  1. Content analysis.
  2. Finding Duplicate and outlier treatment.
  3. Exploratory Dataa Analysis - Relationship between features.
  4. Univariate Analysis - Plotting
  5. Bivariate Analysis - Plotting.
  6. KMeans Clustering - Elbow and Silhoutte score.
  7. Heirarchy Clustering - Dendograms with linkages.
  8. Profiling comparison of kmeans and Heirarchy clustering
  9. Final Recommendation

def custom_round(x, base=30):
    return int(base * round(float(x)/base))

clusters=range(1,9)
meanDistortions=[]

for k in clusters:
    model=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(subset_scaled_df)
    prediction=model.predict(subset_scaled_df)
    distortion=sum(np.min(cdist(subset_scaled_df, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / subset_scaled_df.shape[0]
                           
    meanDistortions.append(distortion)

    print('Number of Clusters:', k, '\tAverage Distortion:', distortion)

plt.plot(clusters, meanDistortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average distortion')
plt.title('Selecting k with the Elbow Method')

For different distance metrics : Euclidean, chebyshevv, Mahalanobis, cityblock and linkage method computing cophenet correlation

In [ ]:
# cophenet index is a measure of the correlation between the distance of points in feature space and distance on dendrogram
# closer it is to 1, the better is the clustering
distance_metrics = [ 'euclidean','chebyshev','mahalanobis','cityblock']
linkage_methods = ['single', 'complete', 'average', 'weighted']
high_cophenet_corr = 0
high_dm_lm = [0,0]
for dm in distance_metrics:
    for lm in linkage_methods:
        Z = linkage(subset_scaled_df, metric=dm, method=lm)
        c, coph_dists = cophenet(Z , pdist(subset_scaled_df))
        print('Cophent correlation for distance metrics {} and linkahe method {} is {}'.format(dm,lm,c))
        if high_cophenet_corr < c:
            high_cophenet_corr = c
            high_dm_lm[0] = dm
            high_dm_lm[1] = lm

for i, method in enumerate(methods):
    
    Z = linkage(subset_scaled_df, metric='euclidean', method=method)

    dendrogram(Z, ax=axs[i]);
    axs[i].set_title(f'Dendrogram ({method.capitalize()} Linkage)')
    coph_corr, coph_dist = cophenet(Z, pdist(subset_scaled_df))
    axs[i].annotate(f'Cophenetic\nCoefficient\n{coph_corr:0.2f}', 
                    (0.80, 0.80),
                    xycoords='axes fraction')
    compare.append([method, coph_corr])

Comparison of Cluster Profile Kmeans vs Heirarchy

  1. Kmeans - has 4 clusters while Heirarchy has 3 clusters.
  2. In Kmeans, cluster 0 and 3 are overlapping but give a dimensional difference based on the visits to banks.
  3. Per Avg Credit limit, for heirarchy has three non-overlapping clusters.
  4. One cluster maps exactly between two methods. The clusters belong to high profile average credit limit.

Since Kmeans profile clusters give more granularity how to improve service to custmers, we can go with Kmeans Clustering

Recommendation for Business and Insights

Approching New Customers

  1. From data it revealed when credit limit increases, the number of visit to bank calls is reduced drastically. visit to bank cost cutomer more money and unhappy.
  2. It is advisable of proviing high credit limit and increase the number of credit card.
  3. Improving online service better, helps customers to resolve quicker and it can save money to the bank.

Overselling Existing customers

  1. Engage the customers to take new additional cards.
  2. Increase the Average credit limit for the credit card holders.
  3. concentrate on cluster - 0 of kmeans and encourage in using online service for the customers.
  4. Improve customer experience on calls made to the bank.
  5. Improve AI to have auto issue resolver via call. There by cluster -1 of kmean will have better service.
